Andy Murray delighted after 'unbelievably tough' Wimbledon win
Andy Murray speaks to Sue Barker on Centre Court after his win in theWimbledon men's singles final,Britain's first for 77 years.The British number one admitted he had "no idea" what happened on the winning point, but said the victory was "especially" for his coach Ivan Lendl.Murray took three hours and 10 minutes to beat top seed Novak Djokovic in straight sets 6-4 7-5 6-4 to win his first Wimbledon title.Available to UK users only.